stories.text: I would like to know what is used to develop a mobile app in 2021. I have a Java/Python background. I have seen Android tutorials but most point to Firebase, I wouldn't like to be tired to any ecosystem. Any pointers for example Kotlin with Mysql/Maria or Postgres db database. Any ideas welcome.

stories.text:
So I just accidentally searched: `https://www.npmjs.com/search?q=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.conventionalcommits.org%2Fen%2Fv1.0.0%2F` and now NPM's web search stopped working with: "looks like something unexpected occurred!".

Called my mate to ask if he could search anything, same error.

And then he checked Twitter and found someone else noticed it too (https://twitter.com/hiyelbaz/status/1463087372070002690).

Did I just affect NPM globally with an odd query string?
stories.title: Ask HN: Did I break just NPM web search?
